  <prompt>
    <goal>Create docs/architecture/code-pages-architecture.md — document React 18 Code Page entry points, auth bootstrap, webpack vs Vite build pipelines, and deployment as Dataverse web resources</goal>
    <context>Code Pages are standalone React 18 SPAs deployed as Dataverse web resources, opened via Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo. They use @spaarke/auth for MSAL bootstrap and call the BFF API. Some use webpack (legacy), others use Vite (preferred). No architecture document captures this pattern end-to-end.</context>
    <constraints>
      - Use /docs-architecture skill structure
      - Source ALL content from actual code — do not invent Code Pages
      - Document every existing Code Page with its purpose and entry point
      - Map the auth bootstrap sequence: resolveRuntimeConfig → setRuntimeConfig → ensureAuthInitialized → render
      - Compare webpack and Vite build pipelines with pros/cons
      - Document deployment as Dataverse web resources (naming, upload, publishing)
      - Cite source files for every Code Page and build config
    </constraints>
  </prompt>
